Executive Summary & Problems That Occurred 3


Troubles that occurred during the project: 
1) I had error message while trying to load the JSON file. The issue was caused by the size and volume of data. SSIS memory could not handle it. The issue was solved by splitting the large JSON file (1.93GB) into smaller files to be able to load the files.

2) I had issue to convert the varchar to bigint to enable the used of aggregate function, after much searching, I discovered some of the values has exponential format. I changed the format and save the file as an excel file. Before loading into the staging area

3)The supplementary dataset does not have a common column with the main table.  Created a derived column MonthCount, within the uspDimCalendarDay using DATEDIFF (MM, @StartDate, @EndDate), to count the month within my start and End date, created the same column in the supplementary dataset matching the Year/Month, and then use a JOIN between the two tables on a common column with same integer ID 



Avoiding potential problems when building a data warehouse
